## Code quality

- Run relevant checks before finishing: `cd apps/web && npm run lint` / `npm run build`; `cd apps/api && ruff check .` / tests for touched apps.
- Prefer useful tests for real behavior; skip trivial tests.
- WS/API contract changes ‚Üí update `docs/realtime-contracts.md` or `docs/architecture.md`.

## Git (agent)

- **Commit or push only when the user explicitly asks.**
- Use Conventional Commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `docs:`, `chore:`.
- Never `--no-verify`, `git config`, or force-push `main` unless explicitly requested.

## PR checklist (before suggesting ‚Äúdone‚Äù)

- [ ] Logic in feature/service/hook, not in route or fat view
- [ ] API via `lib/api`; i18n `en` + `fa` if user-facing strings added
- [ ] No cross-feature imports; no secrets/backups committed
- [ ] Tests or E2E noted if behavior changed
